Find the best equations given a priority order.

Source: R/allo_order.R
allo_order.Rd

This function orders the output of allo_find() by equation type, then reduces it in order, by overwriting equations of each type with the equations of a higher-priority type.

allo_order(.data, order = NULL)

Arguments

.data

List of dataframes. Each should have a rowid column giving the index of each row. Otherwise, rowid will be added with a warning.
order

String giving the name or index of the list elements in the order they should be row-bind, with elements on the left winning over elements on the right.

Value

A dataframe.

See also

rowbind_inorder().

Other functions to manipulate equations: add_equations, allo_evaluate, allo_find, allo_lookup

Examples

allodb::scbi_tree1 %>%
  add_species(allodb::scbi_species, "scbi") %>%
  allo_find() %>%
  allo_order()
